<h2 id="90">8. Automatically refunding PayPal payments</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up an event procedure to automatically refund a PayPal payment.</p>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>Setting up an event procedure</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setup of an event procedure:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Events</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add event procedure</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Create new event procedure</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the event as listed in <a href="#table-procedure-paypal-refund">Table 3</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the settings as listed in <a href="#table-procedure-paypal-refund">Table 3</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the option <strong>Active</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
